 return \\\"hello \\\" + name;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\n../2888-9b720200/human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.interceptor:jboss-interceptor-core:2.0.0.CR1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-09T10-17-59-624448Z.log:1727:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating proxy handling**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how if a proxy's handler is null initially, it gets set to a default object afterward. The array order appears to write sequentially, which is good. I realize I need to implement object array deserialization with the proxy as part of the handler's target. It's also clear that I should check the package name to make sure it keeps things organized outside of the library. Alright, I need to write that file too!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0b73ba4f28eefa020169ff098020308197bc864f218971cfda\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_wmV4RjTMx9muz90fnh7gxPXqvQ1Z09vq9gCw5EJlI3FDWDsV4TagQuSRorlWpEsgyq-pg6k6M3okzacY9aoX3d9TW8MTvTToaZ4s9mCKAfEpqc37V5xHeDBayIMQrH-u0f2LorWJ3EVCnwdGqJFheyvuFnKgTUU-NPGcrdIBFVkbSqw95xrgRIyHnpKeT-pKI4iWlgBKOEgiKwsWQfTWBvqt3nR3l5wMLXsZEdDBXuWUyNKzsNYdsKQqbfZyoPz5aUhpekB04_vfZjppQPJFSUJZB0JPNt3OtMrVUlndNMbEW9cjIxYJDxvhIVgQ0SDDn1brx0SFyxwGgK1zOurCi-uFFUM6dSFW7KRJqA8RDn4SqJBBeM4CKYBWLWShIRycFlTjWw-BVtRvBs0zMcoIMp7ZDKG5FxgVvsZZsbWZpfOHTesGxfcB6wLkyqV5oSyj13T3WBgGzEjJbxFpssDFeYyc3alNWhei5qnF6IsLJgbGTMrN82vdH-xJgk8yppJzRZoBI60JvFtkH4d6iHQktswAPQXCfnWtEQjxkJgfh9iN0z-HiDgJixfa3tx21Fn5jYDRmGUY0Xk64411s16MTgp2fO9jhrRI4kBY8G4H109JF9vF-gdpQIx28zJrLzH9WAS8KbLGE1lDDR6QPVctBCH3ravrE3344tfziR3d4z0gw8igGd6G65tKpp8Pdn8jyMtgSNYDHezH0l-TRpFqIGNFpEUwE5NofU_NySXddIfXeC0Ec2PumAwQb2CJss2VlstVxKBTj4i9vOgFfoe5hvfszBDGfqOQ5pc7H9e2okcyLyRczITvFtiV6ZmIoydP6CHqOX4zHh471AjobF1Cu6CTMRSbn1L98hzD8YgBZaCWrnPdZDxwLZr67KEFRF5Lr1xZ1zp6pK8G1swGaooNPY-mynlnrfRrtFLdSXJVCSgtutX7nQIekwwTNsXh90Oa6sA8IJBXqUM65HgBbeQBRSBvjyElDka5Ke6hBJUK